HEADWORD: midterm
<hw>midterm</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the middle of the
gestation period.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The middle of an academic term or a political term
in office.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An examination given in the middle of an academic
term; a midterm examination.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> midterm examination, midterm exam,
midterm.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mid-thirties</ent>⟦br⟧
